IN THE NEAR FUTURE, GEOSTATIONARY SATELLITES WILL PROVIDE AN UNPRECEDENTED PICTURE OF THE LINKS BETWEEN LOCAL AND REGIONAL EMISSIONS AND THE DISTRIBUTIONS OF TROPOSPHERIC OZONE AND AEROSOLS BY OBSERVING, WITH HIGH SPATIAL AND TEMPORAL DISTRIBUTION, THE TROPOSPHERIC COLUMNS OF A FEW KEY TRACE GASES. HOWEVER, TO OBTAIN A COMPLETE PICTURE OF ATMOSPHERIC CHEMISTRY, MODELS TESTED AGAINST EXTENSIVE CHEMICAL FIELD DATA SETS WILL BE REQUIRED. KORUS AQ IS AN OPPORTUNITY TO PROVIDE SUCH A DATA SET IN A REGION THAT IS CHALLENGING FOR THE MODELS ON THE REGIONAL SCALE AND CRITICAL FOR THE MODELS ON A GLOBAL SCALE. TO TRULY TEST THE PHOTOCHEMICAL MODELS REQUIRES MEASUREMENTS OF HYDROXYL OH, HYDROPEROXYL HO2, AND OH REACTIVITY, WHICH IS THE INVERSE OF THE OH LIFETIME. FOR THESE MEASUREMENTS, WE PROPOSE TO DEPLOY THE AIRBORNE TROPOSPHERIC HYDROGEN OXIDES SENSOR ATHOS AND THE OH REACTIVITY INSTRUMENT OHR ON THE NASA DC8 DURING KORUS AQ. ATHOS MEASUREMENTS HAVE SHOWN THAT OXIDATION CHEMISTRY IS KNOWN TO WITHIN THE UNCERTAINTIES OF THE OBSERVATIONS AND MODELS FOR CLEAN ENVIRONMENTS, BUT FOR MORE COMPLEX ENVIRONMENTS, THE RESULTS ARE MIXED. PART OF THE PROBLEM MAY BE THE MODELS OR AN INCOMPLETE UNDERSTANDING OF THE OXIDATION CHEMISTRY; PART OF THE PROBLEM MAY BE THE MEASUREMENTS THEMSELVES. RECENTLY WE DISCOVERED AN INTERFERENCE IN THE OH MEASUREMENT WITH GROUND-BASED VERSION OF ATHOS AND HAVE IMPLEMENTED CHEMICAL MODULATION, WHICH IS SHOWN TO MEASURE THE REAL OH. THIS METHOD WILL BE IMPLEMENTED ON ATHOS FOR KORUS AQ TO TEST THE HYPOTHESIS THAT THE INTERFERENCE HAS ONLY AFFECTED MEASUREMENTS NEAR FORESTS. ALSO, AS WE DID IN THE DEEP CONVECTIVE CLOUDS AND CHEMISTRY STUDY IN 2012, WE WILL OPERATE ATHOS SO AS TO CLEANLY MEASURE HO2. FOR OH REACTIVITY, WE HAVE LEARNED HOW TO OBTAIN 30 SECOND MEASUREMENTS, WHICH IS A MUCH HIGHER TIME RESOLUTION THAN OUR PREVIOUS TIME RESOLUTION OF 3 MINUTES. WE WILL TEST A BOX MODEL AGAINST THESE DATA. THE BOX MODEL WILL BE CONSTRAINED WITH ALL THE OTHER MEASUREMENTS FROM THE DC8. WE WILL ALSO DETERMINE THE MODEL UNCERTAINTY AND PERFORM A GLOBAL UNCERTAINTY ANALYSIS TO SHOW THOSE COMPONENTS OF THE MODEL THAT DESERVE THE MOST SCRUTINY IN ORDER TO IMPROVE MODEL PERFORMANCE.

doc.ContractDescription: MANNED INTERPLANETARY MISSIONS WILL ONLY BE DESIRABLE ONCE THE ABILITY TO RETURN IS ESTABLISHED. EVEN USING IMPROVED FUEL TECHNOLOGIES WE HAVE NOT RESOURCED THE FUEL REQUIREMENT FOR RETURN MISSIONS TO OUR NEAREST TERRESTRIAL NEIGHBORS. ENERGY HARVESTING IN OUTER SPACE OR ON ANOTHER PLANET IS IMPERATIVE FOR RETURN MISSION SUCCESS, AS IT IS IMPOSSIBLE WITH CURRENT EARTH-BASED FUEL TECHNOLOGIES TO SUPPLY AN OUTGOING MISSION TO OUR CLOSEST NEIGHBOR PLANETS WITH ENOUGH FUEL FOR RETURN. THERMOPHOTOVOLTAIC (TPV) DEVICES, WITH A THEORIZED MAXIMAL E_CIENCY OF 85% CONVERSION OF INCIDENT SUNLIGHT TO ELECTRICITY [1], ARE IDEAL FOR SUCH HARVESTING. THUS, THE WORK I PROPOSE WILL INVESTIGATE PERFORMANCE PARAMETERS OF SELECT TPV MATERIALS. SPECIFICALLY, I WILL STUDY HOW THE OPTICAL ABSORPTION, THERMAL EMISSION, ELECTRONIC ENERGY CONVERSION AND THERMAL TRANSPORT PROPERTIES ARE RELATED TO THE STRUCTURAL FEATURES OF TPV MATERIALS IN THE PRESENCE OF PHOTON WAVELENGTHS ABUNDANT IN THE UNIVERSE. THROUGH AN IN-DEPTH, COMPUTATIONAL AND THEORETICAL, STUDY THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN AMORPHOUS MATERIAL STRUCTURE (I.E., ATOMIC DENSITY AND FRACTAL DIMENSION) AND OPTICAL ABSORPTION, THERMAL EMISSION, ELECTRONIC CONVERSION AND THERMAL TRANSPORT PROPERTIES WILL BE DETERMINED. THE RESULTS WILL ESTABLISH THE GOVERNING MATERIALS PHYSICS TO FURTHER GUIDE MATERIAL SELECTION AND DEVICE DESIGN FOR E_CIENT ELECTROMAGNETIC HARVESTING CELLS TO BE USED FOR CONSTANT REFUEL ON INTERPLANETARY MISSIONS. WE WILL INVESTIGATE ORGANIC SEMICONDUCTING POLYMERS INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO: PCBM, P3HT, AND P3HT:PCBM BLEND THIN FILMS. DUE TO THEIR SMALL BAND GAPS THESE MATERIALS HAVE AN EXTREMELY HIGH CAPACITY FOR ABSORPTION IN THE VISIBLE AND NEAR-IR SPECTRA, WAVELENGTHS ABUNDANT ON THE MARTIAN SURFACE AND IN INTERPLANETARY SPACE. THESE MATERIALS ALSO OFFER LOW THERMAL CONDUCTIVITIES AND CONTROLLABLE FRACTAL-DENDTRITIC GROWTH [2]. WITH FURTHER IMPROVEMENTS TO ENERGY CONVERSION EFFICIENCY, THESE AMORPHOUS ORGANIC MATERIALS OFFER COST-EFFECTIVE AND RELIABLE ALTERNATIVES TO CURRENT STATE-OF-THE-ART TPV DEVICE MATERIALS. ATOMISTIC SIMULATIONS, USING MOLECULAR DYNAMICS AND LATTICE DYNAMICS, AND QUANTUM MECHANICAL CALCULATIONS EMPLOYING NON-EQUILIBRIUM GREENS FUNCTIONS, WILL BE CONDUCTED TO GENERATE PREDICTIONS FOR THE PARAMETERS OF INTEREST MENTIONED PREVIOUSLY. THE TRENDS PREDICTED WITH THE CLASSICAL AND QUANTUM MECHANICAL APPROACHES WILL COMPLIMENT THEORETICAL MODELS WITH THE AIM OF PREDICTING THE ISOLATED EFFECTS OF MICROSTRUCTURE ON THE MATERIAL PROPERTIES. THE DETERMINATION OF THE INTRICACIES IN THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN ATOMIC ARRANGEMENT AND ELECTRONIC AND VIBRATIONAL ACTIVITY ON AN ATOMISTIC LEVEL, FACILITATED BY THE PAIRING OF COMPUTATION AND ANALYTICAL METHODS, WILL BE APPLIED TO THE OPTIMIZATION OF POWER CONVERSION OF TPV DEVICES FOR USE IN OUTER SPACE AND ON THE MARTIAN SURFACE.

doc.ContractDescription: DARK MATTER ANNIHILATION SEARCHES IN DWARF GALAXIES: INTEGRATED CHEMODYNAMICAL MIXTURE MODELING AND GAMMA-RAY ANALYSIS WE REQUEST FUNDING TO PERFORM A COMPLETE OVERHAUL OF CONSTRAINTS ON DARK MATTER ANNIHILATION FROM THE MILKY WAYS DWARF-GALACTIC SATELLITES. FOR A GIVEN EXPOSURE TIME WITH FERMI-LAT, SEARCHES FOR GAMMA-RAY EMISSION AND ENSUING CONSTRAINTS ON THE PARTICLE PHYSICS OF DARK MATTER ARE LIMITED BY OUR ABILITY TO INFER DARK MATTER DENSITIES FROM THE DWARFS INTERNAL STELLAR KINEMATICS. WE HAVE DEVELOPED A NOVEL APPROACH TO THIS PROBLEM, ALLOWING US TO MODEL ALL RELEVANT ASTROPHYSICAL DATA SIMULTANEOUSLY, WHILE AVOIDING SEVERAL ARBITRARY ASSUMPTIONS TO WHICH ALL PREVIOUS ANALYSES HAVE BEEN SENSITIVE. WE PROPOSE TO APPLY THIS NEW ANALYSIS TO ALL KNOWN DWARF GALAXIES (AND/OR TO ANY MORE THAT WILL BE DISCOVERED IN THE NEAR TERM). THE RESULTING CONSTRAINTS ON DARK MATTER DENSITY PROFILES WILL BE THE MOST ROBUST AVAILABLE FOR THESE GALAXIES, AND WE EXPECT THEY WILL BE OF HIGH INTEREST TO THE MANY GROUPS CURRENTLY SEARCHING FERMI DATA FOR SIGNALS OF DARK MATTER ANNIHILATION (AND/OR DECAY). WE WILL ALSO USE THESE RESULTS TO UPDATE OUR OWN GAMMA-RAY ANALYSIS, WHICH RELIES CRITICALLY ON RELATIVE DENSITIES AMONG DWARFS TO OPTIMIZE BOTH 1) SEARCHES FOR EMISSION FROM INDIVIDUAL OBJECTS, AND 2)CONSTRAINTS ON DARK MATTER PARTICLE PROPERTIES FROM A JOINT ANALYSIS OF THE ENTIRE DWARF GALAXY POPULATION.

doc.ContractDescription: SYSTEMATIC SEARCH FOR X-RAY COUNTERPARTS OF FERMI-LAT UNASSOCIATED SOURCES USING SWIFT: NEW BLAZARS, PULSARS, AND MORE WE PROPOSE TO USE SWIFT TO SEARCH FOR X-RAY AND UV/OPTICAL COUNTERPARTS OF UNASSOCIATED 3FGL FERMI-LAT SOURCES. PRIOR PROGRAMS LED TO SWIFT OBSERVATIONS OF 261 AND 199 FERMI UNASSOCIATED SOURCES FROM THE 1FGL AND 2FGL CATALOGS RESPECTIVELY, AS WELL AS INITIAL 3FGL OBSERVATIONS. POSSIBLE X-RAY COUNTERPARTS ARE FOUND IN ~1/3 OF THESE. THESE NEW DATA WILL DETERMINE THE PROPERTIES (WITH ~5 ARCSEC POSITIONS) OF ALL DETECTED X-RAY SOURCES IN THE LAT UNIDENTIFIED 3FGL REGIONS, CONTRIBUTING TO IDENTIFICATION, CLASSIFICATION, AND FOLLOW-UP. THIS PROPOSAL SUPPORTS THE LARGE ANALYSIS AND INTERPRETATION TASK, WHICH WILL REQUIRE ADDITIONAL DATA REDUCTION SOFTWARE. THE SWIFT PI AND EXEC COMMITTEE COMMIT TO THE SWIFT OBSERVING TIME. REDUCED DATA WILL BE MADE PUBLICLY AVAILABLE TO EVERYONE.
